#Kippa App

To configure and test this app; you need the following technologies

1. download and install node js
2. download and setup docker
3. download and set up minikube

Unzip the folder conataining the source code and all other files

navigate to the directory where the project is downloaded and open in terminal.

run `$make default` to build and deploy the application

you need to edit the etc/host file to add the dns name on your machine
use `$sudo -i gedit /etc/hosts` (assuming you use linux)
Note: If you use windows you can see the steps to edit the host file on this link https://www.groovypost.com/howto/edit-hosts-file-windows-10/

You can view the app on `www.kippa.local/profile`
